00:51:20,549 --> 00:51:26,830
Belen gave Xavier's email back to Maggie.

732
00:51:26,830 --> 00:51:31,580
'That's very strange,' she said.

733
00:51:31,580 --> 00:51:38,640
'Maybe he's done something wrong - perhaps
the police are after him or something.'

734
00:51:38,640 --> 00:51:42,500
'No, not Xavier,' said Maggie.

735
00:51:42,500 --> 00:51:44,970
'Why not, Maggie?'

736
00:51:44,970 --> 00:51:46,610
answered Belen.

737
00:51:46,610 --> 00:51:51,549
'I mean, we were only in Chile for three weeks.

738
00:51:51,549 --> 00:51:54,210
How well do we know him?

739
00:51:54,210 --> 00:51:57,730
Have you had any other emails
or letters from him?'

740
00:51:57,730 --> 00:52:05,119
'Yes, an earlier email, but it didn't say
anything about coming to England,' replied

741
00:52:05,119 --> 00:52:06,119
Maggie.

742
00:52:06,119 --> 00:52:13,140
'Oh well, there's nothing you can do - just
wait for the letter and hope it's nothing

743
00:52:13,140 --> 00:52:16,380
bad,' said Belen.

